comments.author: @kelvinmutwiri9646
comments.text:
Do we know that Noni is a RW player? It's the simple inverted wingers. A left footer benefits more when they cut in to their stronger foot.
That LW has not been addressed, hoping Martinelli will rediscover form while embracing his selfish nature won't save that flank. To be effective on the attack, the front three must be a threat independently before becoming one collectively...we can't be strong on the right, middle and then clueless on the left.
We'll continue to get attacked from that side.
If Eze can get in, he can sort himself out efficiently and the balance on front three will be equal or relative...
Until we accept that we have a problem on that LW as we've had before with CF...we'll suffer set backs.
The team has evolved and grown to strengths, we are past hoping a player will be this and that, it's either we know what the player can offer consistently or not.

comments.text:
?is a Portuguese professional footballer and one of the most decorated and celebrated athletes in the history of the sport. Known for his athleticism, prolific goalscoring, and dedication to physical fitness, he is widely regarded as one of the greatest players of all time.
Early Life and Career:
* Born Cristiano Ronaldo dos Santos Aveiro on February 5, 1985, in Funchal, Madeira, Portugal.
* He grew up in an impoverished family and his passion for football was evident from a young age.
* Ronaldo began his professional career at Sporting CP before being signed by Manchester United in 2003.
Major Club Career Highlights:
* Manchester United (2003-2009 & 2021-2022): Under the guidance of Sir Alex Ferguson, he developed into a global superstar. He won three Premier League titles, a UEFA Champions League, and his first Ballon d'Or in 2008.
* Real Madrid (2009-2018): Ronaldo achieved legendary status at Real Madrid, becoming the club's all-time leading scorer with 450 goals in 438 appearances. He won four UEFA Champions League titles, two La Liga crowns, and four more Ballon d'Or awards.
* Juventus (2018-2021): He continued his success in Italy, winning two Serie A titles and scoring over 100 goals for the club.
* Al-Nassr (2023-Present): Ronaldo currently plays for the Saudi Pro League club Al-Nassr.
International Career:
* Ronaldo has been a cornerstone of the Portugal national team since his debut in 2003.
* He is the most-capped male player in international football history and holds the record for the most goals scored at the international level.
* His most significant achievement with the national team was winning the UEFA European Championship in 2016.
Key Achievements and Records:
* Individual: He has won five Ballon d'Or awards, four European Golden Shoes, and has been named FIFA's best player five times.
* Goals: Ronaldo is the all-time leading goalscorer in men's professional football. He holds the records for most goals and assists in the UEFA Champions League.
* Team Trophies: He has won numerous domestic and international titles, including multiple league titles in England, Spain, and Italy, as well as five UEFA Champions League trophies.
